    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1937-12-11T11:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1937-12-11T11:00:00-05:00" n="621"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d621">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">394.115 Panay/15: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in China</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Johnson</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Hankow</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1937-12-12T00:00:00+08:00"
                            >December 12, 1937—[midnight.]</date>
                        <lb/>[Received December 12—1:30 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>2200. Commander Yangtze Patrol has been unable to contact <hi rend="italic"
                        >Panay</hi> since 1335 today. Am informed that Japanese Army forces have
                    orders to fire upon all ships on river. In view of what happened to British
                    naval vessels near Nanking and at Wuhu today, please ask Tokyo to make urgent
                    representations to Foreign Office, and to notify it of whereabouts of <hi
                        rend="italic">Panay</hi> and Standard Oil Company’s ships loaded with
                    American refugees, last reported anchored at mileage 221 above Woosung.</p>
                <p>Peiping repeat urgent to Tokyo. Sent to Peiping and information Cincaf.<note
                        n="51" xml:id="d621fn51">Commander in Chief, United States Asiatic
                        Fleet.</note>
                </p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Johnson</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
